Yeah, so I'm still getting over a cold, which is turing either into a cough or another sore throat.  I have a bad feeling It's gonna be a cough.  My roommate is gonna kill me by the end of this week.  Its raining here which is not a big suprise, after all, it is seattle.  But my sun lamp is keeping me cheery and Amanda is comming up for a weekend so I'm really happy about that.  It will give me a chance to actually explore the city and not be cooped up at my schol like I have been since I got here.  Its not that I'm depress or anything, I just haven't gotten the courage to explore on my own.  Blaise, my roommate is really cool.  We get a long just fine.  My new Dell DJ is my new child.  I take it everywhere I go and it keeps me company on my walks to capitol hill (think of santa monica blvd. mixed with Old Town Pasadena) for a burger at Dick's (An In and Out wannabe but doesn't compare. Can Anyone say Animal Style fries?)  Ok....no more procrastinating!!!!!!!!!!!  I have to do work.

Goodbye sun, good bye warmth!!!  Hello, gloom, rain, and cold!!!!  The last day of sun was two days ago and I was hoping for it to be that way the whole time.  But after all this is Seattle, the city where at UW, RA's have to lock the balcony doors at certain itmes of the year so stressed and depressed kids won't jump to end thier life.  Thankfully, I'm on the other side of town at SU which is brightly painted and has a very warm atmosphere.  No locked balconies here, no seriee.  Everyone is really nice and my classes are great.  In my Epxeriencing Music class, there are doing a section on African Music and certain days, all we do is African Drumming!!!!  Its really fun and every sings and dances and......well drum!  My College Writing class went to play Laser tag.  I think our professor told us it had to do with our class theme (Violence in American Society) but, we all knew that she just wanted to us to have fun.  I got the top score in both games!!!!  That class is also gonna go to the gun range soon.  It's gonna be the first time I've shot a real gun.  I have to admit, I am getting homesick and the weather doesn't help one bit.  Please call, anyone!!!!!

Peace out

So I'm in english class, not listening to a word my teacher is saying while I type this.  I can't wait for friday to come around for two reasons (SHHHHHHHHHHHHH ;))  A word of advice, do not go see the ring two, it is uneventful and not really scary.    And now for something completely different



A boy went to a fortune teller and the fortune teller told him that his father will die in two days.  The boy runs home to tell his mother.  "mom mom, dad going to die in two days you gotta warn him mom! help him"  The mom just looks at his son and says " Son, that fortune teller is just scaring you, you dad is not going to die"  
"But mom he is, he is!!!!!!!"  
"No he is not"

The boy gives up and runs to his dad
"Dad! Dad! you have to do something! a fortune teller told me you were going to die intwo days"  
"Son, you know that the fortune teller is just scaring you.  I'm not going to die anytime soon"
"But dad, I'm scared, I don't want you to die"
"Son I won't"

But the boy was still scared but there was nothing he could do.
SO two days later he wakes up very nervous.  The boy runs into in the kitchen to find both his parents alive and well.  The boy over heard his mom talking about him
"I knew it was just some stupid fortune teller.  He was just scared" The boy let out a breath."But the strange thing is the mailman dropped dead today, very strange"

1. My chemical Romance
2. The Used
3. Chevelle
4. Good Charlotte
5. Papa "motherfucking" Roach
6. Sum 41
7. Social Distortion
8. Incubus (with the police FUCKING AWESOME!)

10. Green Day

Everyone was awesome, but the highlights were Papa Roach and their amazing satanic laughing frenzy, Sum 41 and their elvis skit, Incubus and their jam session with two members of the Police, Velevet Revolver and their godlike reputation to put on a kick ass rock and roll show the world will never see repeated by any other band, and of course Green Day because their are green day and green day is fucking awesome.  (if you;ve been to a green day show you know what I mean.  If you haven't go see them live, It will be the most fun you will ever have besides going to a flogging Molly show OLAY!)  the pit was awesome and the atmosphere was great!
